Wargoszewo  is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Trzebielino, within Bytów County, Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-east of Trzebielino,  north-west of Bytów, and  west of the regional capital Gdańsk.
For details of the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
